<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/41598913-shaista-banu"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1440258407i/41598913._UY100_CR10,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/41598913-shaista-banu">Shaista Banu</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">All through the book one can see that Ka&apos;s character, like that of most people in real-life, is flawed. His personal thoughts also reflect that. Add t<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">All through the book one can see that Ka's character, like that of most people in real-life, is flawed. His personal thoughts also reflect that. Add to that his desperation for Ipek and his intense desire to take her back to Germany with him. Considering these, it is quite possible for him to have revealed Blue's location to the police. Complacent and listless he may have seemed, but what strikes more after his meeting with Ipek is his desperation for a happy life. So, doesn't come across as contradictory to me. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
